8%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20him%2C%20the%20first%20move%20involves%20a%20country%20restructuring%20bad%20debts%20to%20free%20up%20beleaguered%20borrowers%20from%20their%20loan%20commitments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey'll%20have%20to%20be%20spread%20out%20over%20time%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bbalanced%20way%26quot%3B%20to%20avoid%20leaving%20debtors%20out%20to%20dry%20and%20prevent%20a%20sudden%20shock%20to%20the%20economy%2C%20Dalio%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20billionaire%20added%20that%20China%20should%20simultaneously%20lower%20interest%20rates%20to%20encourage%20fresh%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interest%20rate%20cuts%20would%20ideally%20be%20so%20drastic%20that%20they%20run%20below%20inflation%20and%20nominal%20growth%20rates%2C%20Dalio%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20government%20can't%20implement%20that%20policy%2C%20it%20could%20monetize%20debt%20instead%20while%20weakening%20China's%20currency%20to%20lighten%20the%20burden%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20measures%20essentially%20aim%20to%20do%20two%20things%3A%20Give%20China's%20struggling%20borrowers%20%E2%80%94%20of%20which%20there%20are%20now%20many%20%E2%80%94%20some%20breathing%20room%20to%20grow%20their%20businesses%20while%20encouraging%20them%20to%20borrow%20more%20and%20take%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20beautiful%20deleveraging%20can%20only%20be%20done%20in%20countries%20that%20have%20most%20of%20their%20bad%20debts%20denominated%20in%20their%20own%20currencies%20and%20have%20most%20of%20the%20debtors%20and%20creditors%20as%20their%20own%20citizens%2C%20which%20is%20the%20case%20for%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Dalio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bb0a4d86-4a6d-427c-91f9-b9b0ea1cd2d1%5C%22%3EWhy%20China's%20massive%20debt%20is%20seizing%20up%20its%20economy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20economy%20has%20been%20slammed%20by%20swelling%20debt%20levels%20after%20years%20of%20businesses%20and%20local%20governments%20gobbling%20up%20loans%20on%20lax%20interest%2